TO AUTOMATE SELECTING ALL CHECKBOXES IN A PAGE AND SAVE THEM WITH A CLICK ON THE "SAVE" BUTTON IN JAVASCRIPT, YOU CAN FOLLOW THESE STEPS:

1. **SELECT ALL CHECKBOXES**: USE JQUERY OR PURE JAVASCRIPT TO SELECT ALL CHECKBOXES ON THE PAGE.
2. **CHECK EACH CHECKBOX**: ITERATE THROUGH THE SELECTED CHECKBOXES AND CHECK THEM.
3. **HANDLE THE SAVE BUTTON CLICK**: ADD AN EVENT LISTENER TO THE SAVE BUTTON TO AUTOMATICALLY CHECK THE CHECKBOXES WHEN CLICKED.

HERE IS AN EXAMPLE USING JAVASCRIPT:

```javascript
// 1. SELECT ALL CHECKBOXES
const checkboxes = document.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"]');

// 2. CHECK EACH CHECKBOX
checkboxes.forEach(checkbox => {
    checkbox.checked = true; // This will check all checkboxes
});

// 3. HANDLE THE SAVE BUTTON CLICK
document.getElementById('saveButton').addEventListener('click', function() {
    // The checkboxes are already checked, so no need to do anything here
    console.log("All checkboxes are checked and ready to save.");
});
```

IF YOU ARE USING JQUERY, HERE IS HOW YOU CAN DO IT:

```javascript
// 1. SELECT ALL CHECKBOXES
const checkboxes = $('input[type="checkbox"]');

// 2. CHECK EACH CHECKBOX
checkboxes.prop('checked', true); // This will check all checkboxes

// 3. HANDLE THE SAVE BUTTON CLICK
$('#saveButton').on('click', function() {
    // The checkboxes are already checked, so no need to do anything here
    console.log("All checkboxes are checked and ready to save.");
});
```

IN BOTH CASES, MAKE SURE THAT THE `saveButton` ID EXISTS IN YOUR HTML:

```html
<button id="saveButton">Save</button>
```

THIS WAY, WHEN YOU CLICK THE "SAVE" BUTTON, ALL THE CHECKBOXES WILL BE AUTOMATICALLY CHECKED AND READY FOR YOU TO SAVE.

